•	Over 60% of respondents in urban India attributed hair fall and dryness to hard water.
	•	In cities like Bengaluru and Delhi, nearly 70% of households reported visible hair damage from daily water use.

Hard water effects on hair : 

1. Makes Hair Dry and Brittle

The minerals in hard water can coat the hair shaft, making it difficult for moisture to penetrate. This can leave your hair feeling dry, rough, and more prone to breakage.

2. Causes Buildup

Hard water causes mineral buildup on your scalp and hair. This residue can:
	•	Weigh hair down
	•	Make it look dull or lifeless
	•	Interfere with the effectiveness of shampoos and conditioners

3. Leads to Itchy Scalp or Dandruff 
4. ⁠ Mineral deposits can irritate the scalp, potentially leading to dryness, itchiness, or flaking.

5. Reduces Hair Volume and Shine : 

Buildup from hard water can make your hair feel limp and greasy even after washing, and reduce natural shine.

Healing the gut involves reducing inflammation, restoring the gut lining, and supporting a healthy balance of gut bacteria. Here’s howabove mentioned food help :

1 ) black coffee : Coffee contains polyphenols, plant compounds that feed good gut bacteria and support a healthy gut ecosystem. (NOTE : never drink black coffee empty stomach, also consumption in moderation is helpful) 

2) carrots & cucumber(vegges) : basically we need to add high fibre food to our diet! 

3) yogurt : an easy probiotic in every Indian household . Yogurt helps replenish good bacteria like Lactobacillus and Bifidobacterium.

4) almonds & walnuts : both are sources of good fats. Almonds contain vitamin E and antioxidants. which can help protect and support the gut lining. 

5) flax & chia seeds : rich in omega 3 help reduce inflammation in gut. they are the cheapest & easiest food that help with gut !
